= Prussian State Elections

Elections to the Landtag of Prussia have been held on the same day as those to the Reichstag, and have unsurprisingly returned an SPD victory. We have retained a mandate to continue our current, and preferred, Weimar Coalition with the Center Party and DDP.

However, with greater ambitions on his mind, the Center's Adam Stegerwald seems to have an eye out to lead this next Prussian Cabinet.

Additionally, we could also bring the DVP into our government. They would shift the balance of power away from us, but this move would improve our relations with them, and perhaps the bourgeois as a whole.

We are expected to retain Otto Braun as the Minister-President of Prussia, but, ultimately, the balance of power is in the SPD's hands.

