The DVP helps us establish a stronger majority, and bringing in another bourgeois coalition partner will greatly please the middle class, with talks of a "balancing act" and "moderation. On the other hand, it helps the SPD in no way, and the party's membership knows that.

At least, Braun remains in charge of the Prussian government -- or so it seems.
